      "id": "PopularPost277802",
      "post_content": "Were you to be handed a pack of each of the 5 guildmages to first pack first pick in a draft, you would be a fool not to windmill slam this guy right here. Shutting off whatever crucial permanent your opponent may have in play gives you a ridiculous amount of time to create a situation in which you can punch through, or simply release the floodgates with this guy detaining something every turn. All of the mages have their uses, but none are as universally useful as telling your opponent's bomb rare to sit down and shut up. Others may be more revered and be more sexy to think about in casual formats and the such, but never pass this guy up unless you are straight up going to feed the player next to you the Azorius deck.",
      "posted_by": "WokeUpDead",
