      "id": "PopularPost365291",
      "post_content": "I love detain because its an action, not just a regular keyword. I love detaining things, it just feels thematic and fun. This is the only card in the game with an activated ability to detain, so I will play it regardless of the cost. I do like being able to hit artifacts and planeswalkers with it, so I will gladly pay the 5 in casual and EDH. Still, Detain feels right on activated abilities, so why is this the only one?   \n  \nI know W/U does ETB effects, and that's great and all, but I wish I had some more reusable detain without abusing flicker. A creature or artifact with the ability to tap to detain would be nice.",
      "posted_by": "Enelysios",
